node.text: Glow gang ☄️☄️☄️ what a way to finish, I’m honestly so greatful for you guys & you should be so so proud 🥲 making sustainable habbits for life 🙌🏼 Thank you again for all the love & kind messages over the last 66 days 🤍 if you didn’t start the challenge with me don’t worry, you can start from the beginning as it’s saved down to my App. What a way to finish, your favourite exercises 🙌🏼🙌🏼 you guys are glowing ☄️☄️☄️

node.text: As we head into the last full week of my @weglow 66 day challenge I wanted to reshare my own story 🧡 It has felt like such a privilege to be able to share with you all the stories of these incredible women over the past 8 weeks. I truly hope that all of these “Stories that Glow” have brought some light to your Sunday’s & that you might have seen something of yourself in these women 🙏🏻 Remember ~ you glow from the inside out ✨

node.text: As we head into the last full week of my @weglow 66 day challenge I wanted to reshare my own story 🧡 It has felt like such a privilege to be able to share with you all the stories of these incredible women over the past 8 weeks. I truly hope that all of these “Stories that Glow” have brought some light to your Sunday’s & that you might have seen something of yourself in these women 🙏🏻 Remember ~ you glow from the inside out ✨

node.text: I can’t believe we’re heading into the last two weeks of the  @weglow 66 day challenge 🤩 I’ve loved being on this journey with you all and watching you glow. You should be so proud 🧡 As usual, this evening I want to bring you more light & motivation as we head into the next week, now I feel we need it more than ever✨ Today’s story is from @hannahcleeve - who is such a pure soul & the way this superstar moves is just out of this world, I’m in total awe of her 🙏🏻 Hannah’s words resonate with me so much & I hope you can all take something from them too. Please take a moment to listen or read what she has to say & tag someone that needs to hear this 🥰 @hannahcleeve

node.text: Let me introduce you to the incredible @trishp16 who reached out to me over a year ago. She told me her story & how she had started using my workouts once she was recovering ✨ Her story instantly touched me & so I immediately asked her to be involved in @weglow’s Stories that Glow campaign. I am genuinely so honoured to be able to share her story with you all today. Please have a listen & I hope Trish’s story inspires you as much as it does for me - she is a true fighter who we can all take a lot of positivity & strength from ✨ Tag someone who might need to hear or read this today 🧡

node.text:
Happy Valentine’s Day everyone; I hope today’s “Stories that Glow” reminds you to work on loving yourself today - as the most important relationship you’ll ever have is the one you have with yourself ❤️

This weeks story is about the  incredibly talented Sophie @sophcaz ⚡️ and her journey to find what truly helps her to glow from the inside out. I was so excited to meet Sophie, a GB athlete (brings back sporting memories & team moral) 🙌🏼 Sophie is so down to Earth, chatty and just exudes confidence in her own skin and who she is ✨ So if you can spare a few minutes to watch & listen between scrolling I guarantee you’ll come away glowing 🧡

“Who got you smiling like that?” Iced 🍵 
The matcha I always use is either @clearspringuk or @t2tea_uk & ALWAYS with @rudehealth health almond drink (go for the drink not milk) or the one I did on @weglow with strawberries was @oatly oat milk as my my preference with strawberries 🍓 for this one just add hot water to the 🍵 first make sure it’s not bitty so whisk well then add ice & milk 🤍 I drink it almost every morning, hot or iced instead of coffee it settles my tummy & gives me a sustained energy boost, have you guys tried it? 🤍
